<TITLE> SKOP urges payment of workers' arrears ahead of Eid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 14 (bdnews24.com) Labour organisation Sramik Karmachari Oikya Parishad (SKOP) has demanded payment of all salary arrears to workers of all industries and factories, by the 25th day of Ramadan. SKOP leaders made the demand at a press conference at the organisation's temporary headquarters at Topkhana Road on Sunday. Member secretary Shahidul Islam said: "We are urging the owners to pay all arrears, including the current month and Eid bonuses, to workers in all industries and factories by the 25th of Ramadan." "We also request the government to take necessary steps in this regard." Convenor of the organisation, Shah Atiul Islam read out a written statement at the press conference, which also demanded immediate full withdrawal of all bans and conditions on trade union activities "to maintain stability and development in industries". bdnew
